# 2️⃣ Stack & Queue Using Linked Lists

This is a favorite interview topic.

---

# First Understand the Big Idea

We already learned:

### Stack

```text
LIFO
Last In First Out
```

Example:

```text
Plate Stack
```

---

### Queue

```text
FIFO
First In First Out
```

Example:

```text
Ticket Queue
```

---

Interviewers often ask:

> "Can you implement them using Linked Lists?"

Let's understand WHY.

---

# A. Stack Using Linked List

---

# Stack Operations

Need:

```text
push()
pop()
top()
```

---

# Key Idea

Use:

```text
Head = Top of Stack
```

---

# Example

Initially:

```text
NULL
```

---

Push 10:

```text
10 → NULL
```

---

Push 20:

```text
20 → 10 → NULL
```

---

Push 30:

```text
30 → 20 → 10 → NULL
```

---

Notice:

Newest element always at head.

Perfect for stack.

---

# Why?

Insertion at head is:

```text
O(1)
```

Very fast.

---

# Pop Operation

Current:

```text
30 → 20 → 10
```

Pop:

Remove head.

Result:

```text
20 → 10
```

Again:

```text
O(1)
```

---

# Mental Model

```text
Stack
=
Add/remove from same end
```

Linked list handles this beautifully.

---

# Stack Complexity

| Operation | Complexity |
| --------- | ---------- |
| Push      | O(1)       |
| Pop       | O(1)       |
| Top       | O(1)       |

---

# B. Queue Using Linked List

---

# Queue Operations

Need:

```text
enqueue()
dequeue()
```

---

# Key Idea

Maintain:

```text
Front Pointer
Rear Pointer
```

---

# Example

Initially:

```text
Front = NULL
Rear  = NULL
```

---

Enqueue 10:

```text
Front
  ↓
10
  ↑
Rear
```

---

Enqueue 20:

```text
Front
 ↓
10 → 20
      ↑
     Rear
```

---

Enqueue 30:

```text
Front
 ↓
10 → 20 → 30
           ↑
          Rear
```

---

# Dequeue

Remove from front.

After removing 10:

```text
Front
 ↓
20 → 30
      ↑
     Rear
```

---

# Why Two Pointers?

Without rear pointer:

Adding new elements becomes slow.

With rear pointer:

```text
enqueue = O(1)
```

---

# Queue Complexity

| Operation | Complexity |
| --------- | ---------- |
| Enqueue   | O(1)       |
| Dequeue   | O(1)       |

---

# Real-World Example

Food delivery orders:

```text
Order1
Order2
Order3
```

First order placed:

```text
First order served
```

Queue behavior.

---

